			<div id="support">
				<h2>Support</h2>
				<div class="border-left">
	<h3>To Un-Install the Plugin:</h3>
	</div>
<p>
Remove all files in the plugin package.
</p>
<p>
Restore your backup for <span class="tomato-txt">includes/templates/YOUR_TEMPLATE/common/tpl_main_page.php</span>.</p>
<p>
Restore your <span class="tomato-txt">includes/templaes/YOUR_TEMPLATE/css/index_home.css</span> file.
</p>

			</div>
			<div id="install">
				<h2>Extract Zips</h2>
				<p>You should now have two zip files:
				<ol><li>Your site backup</li>
				<li>The add-on download</li>
				</ol>
				</p>
				<p>Extract both to a convenient location. (After this step, you should see both the zip file and the extracted folders in your directory.)</p>
				<br>
				<div>   ├── common<br />
   ├── css<br />
   ├── info_shopping_cart<br />
   └── templates</div>
			</div>
